I have added information about the controversies in which Manuela Picq has been involved in Ecuador.

It's an encyclopedia, and the photos posted here must have historical value for the article. It's not Instagram; it doesn't matter if a photo has more megapixels or if someone looks more 'handsome' in a Lasso photo. The goal of Wikipedia is not to gain followers.

Your arguments are ridiculous; the number of megapixels does not define the quality of an image, especially if that image lacks any historical value. I suppose you'll also delete photos from World War II because they don't have many megapixels.

The image quality (based solely on megapixels) is irrelevant when one photo carries a significant story and another does not. And it is you who is waging war, reversing changes without a proper justification beyond the megapixel count.
In an Encyclopedia, priority should be given to images of greater importance or historical significance, rather than those with higher megapixels. The photo is for Wikipedia, not Instagram.
This picture is from when he was inaugurated as president and is more representative.
